<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-03-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-03-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="127" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Stevens</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 17.]</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-03-04"><hi rend="italic">March 4,
                                        1890</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of
                                your confidential dispatch (No. 17) of the 7th ultimo, touching the
                                result of the late election in the Hawaiian Islands, and its
                                probable effect on the interests of the United States. It has been
                                read with attention.</p>
                            <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">James G.
                                Blaine.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>